<br>
So basically, unless you want to camp an entire raid and fight in with a second raid, and hop each other on alternate days waiting for the key mobs to respawn, you are down to three and a half groups at best by the time you get anywhere at all in Sky.  And that just isn't going to cut it by the time you get near the end.  Corpse summoning between islands becomes vital, not optional.<br>
<br>
So no, I haven't completely dismissed, in theory, the idea of doing Sky with no summoner.  If your raid whiped you could mount a rescue raid the next day maybe, and try to make sure each and every person on the previous raid was up to be rezzed.  But in practise?  Pretty damn near impossible.<br>
<br>
In the end, you have to allow that this is a game and people want to have fun, and the limitations they will accept just for the sake of an absolutely purist approach are, finally, limited.  I'm not going to get into a dick waving contest with evil raiders over who is more &quot;pure&quot; in terms of their raids, I'm just going to say what we do is, I believe, pretty damn near as close as anyone ever gets to pure good/neutral raiding into planar raids and beyond.  And that, in my books, is an accomplishment I'll stand on.<br>
<br>
