<br>
The only way it really becomes easy to keep up CoV is if your guild is the only one doing AoW or you have a nice set of guilds and none mind if you visit for a faction tap on him.  He's a huge boost to CoV.  If you get him every week, he's more than enough to eliminate any need for dull Kael factioning.<br>
<br>
I've heard rez goo still drops, too.  I've yet too see one, though.  That's what I meant.  Possible, but not practical.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=witherweaver>Witherweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 354<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/10/02 4:47:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1951.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmm, I don't see any difference ..</span><hr size=1> Don't worry about yard trash hits, go off and FD or /q out the big mobs.  Your faction goes down fairly slowly, and you don't need to venture into Kael that often.  Likely your guild is going to at some point want to take out Vindi/Statue/Idol/AoW/KT so you'll end up getting some positive hits.  If you already kill in Kael, having a considerably larger faction buffer means you (possibly) don't have to spend extra time in Kael because the time that you already spend is sufficient.<br>
<br>
There's an extreme benefit for someone that can FD (usually the pulling monk) to obtain CoV faction, because you can drag corpses throughout most of ToV without getting plowed (FD dragging, obviously).  If you don't have a mage on CoV faction, and happen to have rez goos or vox sticks, you can drag up a cleric and mage to the hallways before Eashan to buff and organize for Eashan/Aary/NToV/etc.<br>
<br>
Having someone maintain CoV faction is helpful if you like playing around in ToV.  Having that person being able to FD is very helpful because he can do corpse runs in many cases.  I generalized and called this person the puller, realizing that in some situations the puller would probably find it convenient to not be KoS (Lendi I would guess).<br>
<br>
I've witnessed people using rez goos before for this kind of idea; they do drop.<br>
